  "review_sentences": [
    {
      "review_id": "ryg4Fgr9hX",
      "sentence_index": 0,
      "text": "This paper proposes an extension to the continual learning framework using existing variational continual learning (VCL) as the base method.",
      "suffix": "",
      "review_action": "arg_structuring",
      "fine_review_action": "arg-structuring_summary",
      "aspect": "none",
      "polarity": "none"
    },
    {
      "review_id": "ryg4Fgr9hX",
      "sentence_index": 1,
      "text": "In particular, it proposes to use the weight of evidence (WE) (from Zintgraf et al 2017) for each task.",
      "suffix": "",
      "review_action": "arg_structuring",
      "fine_review_action": "arg-structuring_summary",
      "aspect": "none",
      "polarity": "none"
    },
    {
      "review_id": "ryg4Fgr9hX",
      "sentence_index": 2,
      "text": "Firstly, this WE can be used to visualize the learned model (as used in Zintgraf et. al. 2017).",
      "suffix": "",
      "review_action": "arg_structuring",
      "fine_review_action": "arg-structuring_summary",
      "aspect": "none",
      "polarity": "none"
    },
    {
      "review_id": "ryg4Fgr9hX",
      "sentence_index": 3,
      "text": "The novelty of this paper is:",
      "suffix": "\n",
      "review_action": "arg_structuring",
      "fine_review_action": "arg-structuring_heading",
      "aspect": "none",
      "polarity": "none"
    },
    {
      "review_id": "ryg4Fgr9hX",
      "sentence_index": 4,
      "text": "1. to use this WE from the current task to generate a silence map (by smoothing the WE) for the next task.",
      "suffix": "",
      "review_action": "arg_structuring",
      "fine_review_action": "arg-structuring_summary",
      "aspect": "none",
      "polarity": "none"
    },
    {
      "review_id": "ryg4Fgr9hX",
      "sentence_index": 5,
      "text": "This is interpreted the learned the learned attention region.",
      "suffix": "",
      "review_action": "arg_structuring",
      "fine_review_action": "arg-structuring_summary",
      "aspect": "none",
      "polarity": "none"
    },
    {
      "review_id": "ryg4Fgr9hX",
      "sentence_index": 6,
      "text": "Such an approach is named Interpretable COntinual Learning (ICL)",
      "suffix": "\n",
      "review_action": "arg_structuring",
      "fine_review_action": "arg-structuring_summary",
      "aspect": "none",
      "polarity": "none"
    },
    {
      "review_id": "ryg4Fgr9hX",
      "sentence_index": 7,
      "text": "2. The paper proposes a metric for the saliency map naming FSM which is an extension of existing metric SSR.",
      "suffix": "",
      "review_action": "arg_structuring",
      "fine_review_action": "arg-structuring_summary",
      "aspect": "none",
      "polarity": "none"
    },
    {
      "review_id": "ryg4Fgr9hX",
      "sentence_index": 8,
      "text": "The extension is to take pixel count to compute the area instead of using rectangular region area, as well as taking the distance between pixels into account.",
      "suffix": "",
      "review_action": "arg_structuring",
      "fine_review_action": "arg-structuring_summary",
      "aspect": "none",
      "polarity": "none"
    },
    {
      "review_id": "ryg4Fgr9hX",
      "sentence_index": 9,
      "text": "This metric can be used to evaluate the level of catastrophic forgetting.",
      "suffix": "\n\n",
      "review_action": "arg_structuring",
      "fine_review_action": "arg-structuring_summary",
      "aspect": "none",
      "polarity": "none"
    },
    {
      "review_id": "ryg4Fgr9hX",
      "sentence_index": 10,
      "text": "Pro:",
      "suffix": "\n",
      "review_action": "arg_structuring",
      "fine_review_action": "arg-structuring_heading",
      "aspect": "none",
      "polarity": "none"
    },
    {
      "review_id": "ryg4Fgr9hX",
      "sentence_index": 11,
      "text": "In general, the idea is very intuitive and make sense.",
      "suffix": "",
      "review_action": "arg_evaluative",
      "fine_review_action": "none",
      "aspect": "asp_motivation-impact",
      "polarity": "pol_positive"
    },
    {
      "review_id": "ryg4Fgr9hX",
      "sentence_index": 12,
      "text": "The paper also demonstrates superior performance with the proposed method on continual learning on all classic tasks comparing with VCL and EWC.",
      "suffix": "\n",
      "review_action": "arg_evaluative",
      "fine_review_action": "none",
      "aspect": "asp_substance",
      "polarity": "pol_positive"
    },
    {
      "review_id": "ryg4Fgr9hX",
      "sentence_index": 13,
      "text": "The presentation is very easy to follow.",
      "suffix": "\n",
      "review_action": "arg_evaluative",
      "fine_review_action": "none",
      "aspect": "asp_clarity",
      "polarity": "pol_positive"
    },
    {
      "review_id": "ryg4Fgr9hX",
      "sentence_index": 14,
      "text": "It seems like a valid and flexible extension that can be used in other continual learning frameworks.",
      "suffix": "\n\n",
      "review_action": "arg_evaluative",
      "fine_review_action": "none",
      "aspect": "asp_motivation-impact",
      "polarity": "pol_positive"
    },
    {
      "review_id": "ryg4Fgr9hX",
      "sentence_index": 15,
      "text": "Cons:",
      "suffix": "\n",
      "review_action": "arg_structuring",
      "fine_review_action": "arg-structuring_heading",
      "aspect": "none",
      "polarity": "none"
    },
    {
      "review_id": "ryg4Fgr9hX",
      "sentence_index": 16,
      "text": "The theoretical contribution is very limited.",
      "suffix": "",
      "review_action": "arg_evaluative",
      "fine_review_action": "none",
      "aspect": "asp_originality",
      "polarity": "pol_negative"
    },
    {
      "review_id": "ryg4Fgr9hX",
      "sentence_index": 17,
      "text": "The work is rather incremental from current state-of-the-art methods.",
      "suffix": "\n",
      "review_action": "arg_evaluative",
      "fine_review_action": "none",
      "aspect": "asp_originality",
      "polarity": "pol_negative"
    },
    {
      "review_id": "ryg4Fgr9hX",
      "sentence_index": 18,
      "text": "There should be a better discussion of related work on the topic.",
      "suffix": "",
      "review_action": "arg_evaluative",
      "fine_review_action": "none",
      "aspect": "asp_meaningful-comparison",
      "polarity": "pol_negative"
    },
    {
      "review_id": "ryg4Fgr9hX",
      "sentence_index": 19,
      "text": "The paper currently only mentions the most related work for the proposed method,  using the whole section 2 to describe VCL and use section 3 to describe FSM and half of section 5 to describe SSR.",
      "suffix": "",
      "review_action": "arg_evaluative",
      "fine_review_action": "none",
      "aspect": "asp_meaningful-comparison",
      "polarity": "pol_negative"
    },
    {
      "review_id": "ryg4Fgr9hX",
      "sentence_index": 20,
      "text": "A general overview of related work in these directions are needed.",
      "suffix": "\n\n",
      "review_action": "arg_request",
      "fine_review_action": "arg-request_edit",
      "aspect": "asp_clarity",
      "polarity": "none"
    },
    {
      "review_id": "ryg4Fgr9hX",
      "sentence_index": 21,
      "text": "Other:",
      "suffix": "\n",
      "review_action": "arg_structuring",
      "fine_review_action": "arg-structuring_heading",
      "aspect": "none",
      "polarity": "none"
    },
    {
      "review_id": "ryg4Fgr9hX",
      "sentence_index": 22,
      "text": "1. The paper should also consider more recently proposed evaluation metrics such as discussed in https://arxiv.org/pdf/1805.09733.pdf",
      "suffix": "\n",
      "review_action": "arg_request",
      "fine_review_action": "arg-request_experiment",
      "aspect": "asp_replicability",
      "polarity": "none"
    },
    {
      "review_id": "ryg4Fgr9hX",
      "sentence_index": 23,
      "text": "2. The author should try to avoid using yellow color in plots.",
      "suffix": "",
      "review_action": "arg_request",
      "fine_review_action": "arg-request_edit",
      "aspect": "asp_clarity",
      "polarity": "none"
    }
  ],
